## Political Effects of Globalization

### Positive Political Effects

1. **International Cooperation and Peace**  
   Globalization has strengthened international institutions (UN, WTO, EU, ASEAN) that promote peace, reduce conflict risk, and foster cooperation on global challenges such as climate change and pandemics ([Burlacu et al., 2018](https://netivist.org)).

2. **Support for Human Rights and Democracy**  
   International organizations often advocate for freedom, human rights, and governance reforms, providing aid and monitoring abuses ([Edusson, 2021](https://ivypanda.com/essays/advantages-and-disadvantages-of-globalization/)).

3. **Empowerment of Smaller States**  
   Through regional blocs and international forums, smaller countries can amplify their influence and collaborate on shared interests ([Burlacu et al., 2018](https://netivist.org)).

### Negative Political Effects

1. **Erosion of State Sovereignty**  
   Global governance and supranational institutions can limit national autonomy in policymaking, sometimes leading to democratic deficits and accountability issues ([Burlacu et al., 2018](https://netivist.org)).

2. **Dominance of Powerful States**  
   Larger countries often wield disproportionate influence in international organizations, skewing decisions to their advantage ([Edusson, 2021](https://ivypanda.com/essays/advantages-and-disadvantages-of-globalization/)).

3. **Complexity and Inefficiency**  
   Coordination among numerous actors is costly and slow, sometimes hindering timely responses to global crises ([Burlacu et al., 2018](https://netivist.org)).

